WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
All right, final item of the Galactic Defiance meeting.

2
00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:10.000
Our plan to take out the Gromphlamite Queen.

3
00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:15.000
Quiet! We could be a defiance without talking over each other.

4
00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:17.000
Thank you.

5
00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:18.000
Karsika?

6
00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:22.000
As it stands, our assassination task force has yet to provide a clear plan.

7
00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:26.000
We provide lots of plans. Your committee keeps killing them.

8
00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:29.000
Well, it's an assassination committee. What do you want them to do?

9
00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:32.000
All intelligence indicates that needs to be a surprise.

10
00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:34.000
Which is why we need to plan it carefully.

11
00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:37.000
Why don't we turn things over to our assassin, Bet Sanchez?

12
00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:43.000
Great. It's an assassination meeting. Where the hell is the assassin?

13
00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:46.000
Beth, where are you?

14
00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:47.000
Um, assassinating?

15
00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:50.000
Are you insane? We're still in a meeting about this.

16
00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:53.000
We've been meeting about it for months. Is the plan to kill her with old age?

17
00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:56.000
There is no plan. We still have to approve one.

18
00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:58.000
Do you even look at your defiance email?

19
00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:01.000
We're in a meeting about assassinations for three-factor authentication.

20
00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:16.000
The defiance says hello.

21
00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:18.000
Or goodbye?

22
00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:22.000
I mean, I guess the hello meant goodbye anyway, but this guy beat me to it?

23
00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:25.000
Oh, my God! Who are you, an assassin?

24
00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:27.000
I mean, I wish.

25
00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:29.000
Ah!

26
00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:35.000
Time to go.

27
00:01:37.000 --> 00:01:39.000
Oh, shit.

28
00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:43.000
Uh, hey, good news. The Queen is dead. Bad news. I didn't do it. Worse news, I need a left.

29
00:01:43.000 --> 00:01:46.000
I can't approve an extraction from an unapproved assassination.

30
00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:48.000
I'll have to call an emergency meeting.

31
00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:50.000
I'm going to die.

32
00:01:57.000 --> 00:01:59.000
Ah!

33
00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:34.420
A

34
00:02:34.420 --> 00:02:38.000
restaurant in Chikan is said to be the best place to be.

35
00:02:38.000 --> 00:02:40.000
Whoa. You beat out Luigi's.

36
00:02:43.000 --> 00:02:45.000
I'm hammering sushi. What's up?

37
00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:48.000
Oh, uh, funny story. Or maybe not that funny.

38
00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:50.000
Are you pitching a Hulu original?

39
00:02:50.000 --> 00:02:53.000
I... I kinda...

40
00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:56.000
went rogue and out trapped on a girl for my show.

41
00:02:56.000 --> 00:02:57.880
trapped in a girlfriend's light ship?

42
00:02:57.880 --> 00:02:59.720
Send the coordinates, I'll pick you up.

43
00:02:59.720 --> 00:03:01.120
Really? Just like that?

44
00:03:01.120 --> 00:03:02.280
Of course, just like that.

45
00:03:02.280 --> 00:03:03.840
You're my daughter, probably.

46
00:03:03.840 --> 00:03:05.600
Jiro, lava cake to go.

47
00:03:05.600 --> 00:03:07.160
The lava cake was already ordered.

48
00:03:07.160 --> 00:03:08.000
I can see it from here.

49
00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:10.680
You don't have to explain.

50
00:03:10.680 --> 00:03:12.880
You're thinking it'd be easy to scan the only warm-blooded

51
00:03:12.880 --> 00:03:13.680
thing on the ship?

52
00:03:13.680 --> 00:03:14.680
We tried that once.

53
00:03:14.680 --> 00:03:15.760
Lot of rats in the walls.

54
00:03:15.760 --> 00:03:17.920
Is that why the ship always has a B in the window?

55
00:03:20.800 --> 00:03:21.800
Hey, freeze!

56
00:03:21.800 --> 00:03:24.040
You first.

57
00:03:24.040 --> 00:03:27.880
Block right into it.

58
00:03:27.880 --> 00:03:29.920
Wow, Beth, you've been staying busy.

59
00:03:29.920 --> 00:03:31.880
Oh, shit, it's Rick Sanchez.

60
00:03:31.880 --> 00:03:33.680
My daughter is just as dangerous.

61
00:03:38.560 --> 00:03:40.240
Wait, so the gun also shoots a sign?

62
00:03:40.240 --> 00:03:41.240
Yeah, for clarity.

63
00:03:41.240 --> 00:03:43.480
So people know it's quicksand and not a brown portal

64
00:03:43.480 --> 00:03:44.440
or diarrhea.

65
00:03:44.440 --> 00:03:46.200
But doesn't the sign tip off the enemy?

66
00:03:46.200 --> 00:03:46.600
No, no, no.

67
00:03:46.600 --> 00:03:48.560
The other side says ordinary sand.

68
00:03:48.560 --> 00:03:49.560
There she is!

69
00:03:50.560 --> 00:03:51.560
Oh, what?

70
00:03:51.560 --> 00:03:52.560
Oh, oh, oh!

71
00:03:52.560 --> 00:03:54.560
See, there's your classic diary.

72
00:03:54.560 --> 00:03:55.560
Yeah.

73
00:03:55.560 --> 00:03:56.560
Whatever, can we go now?

74
00:03:56.560 --> 00:03:57.560
Just portal me to HQ.

75
00:03:57.560 --> 00:04:00.560
Actually, could you portal me, like, block away?

76
00:04:00.560 --> 00:04:01.560
So they don't know your dad drove you?

77
00:04:01.560 --> 00:04:02.560
Sure.

78
00:04:02.560 --> 00:04:06.560
OK, all in favor of Natalie thumb-nailing an emergency rescue

79
00:04:06.560 --> 00:04:07.560
budget?

80
00:04:07.560 --> 00:04:08.560
Oh!

81
00:04:08.560 --> 00:04:09.560
Oh, whoops.

82
00:04:09.560 --> 00:04:10.560
You're a prick.

83
00:04:10.560 --> 00:04:11.560
Stop acting embarrassed.

84
00:04:11.560 --> 00:04:12.560
I'm a legend here.

85
00:04:12.560 --> 00:04:14.560
Oh, hey, Buggan.

86
00:04:14.560 --> 00:04:15.560
Hey, Rick.

87
00:04:15.560 --> 00:04:18.560
Yes, it's disappointing that the legend doesn't fall far from

88
00:04:18.560 --> 00:04:19.560
the tree.

89
00:04:19.560 --> 00:04:20.560
Huh.

90
00:04:20.560 --> 00:04:21.560
That's a weird way to thank her and apologize.

91
00:04:21.560 --> 00:04:22.560
Dad!

92
00:04:22.560 --> 00:04:23.560
Thank her for what?

93
00:04:23.560 --> 00:04:24.560
A botched assassination?

94
00:04:24.560 --> 00:04:25.560
Whoa, whoa.

95
00:04:25.560 --> 00:04:26.560
I don't botch shit.

96
00:04:26.560 --> 00:04:27.560
I just turned down sloppy seconds.

97
00:04:27.560 --> 00:04:30.560
Yeah, their mothership wasn't on red alert for her birthday.

98
00:04:30.560 --> 00:04:32.560
You sure about that?

99
00:04:32.560 --> 00:04:34.560
Red alert for the queen's birthday.

100
00:04:34.560 --> 00:04:35.560
That's right.

101
00:04:35.560 --> 00:04:39.560
Her majesty is 70 days young, but still laying eggs and fanging

102
00:04:39.560 --> 00:04:40.560
drones.

103
00:04:40.560 --> 00:04:41.560
You go, girl.

104
00:04:41.560 --> 00:04:42.560
Yes, queen.

105
00:04:42.560 --> 00:04:44.560
No, I saw that bitch's pillow through her face.

106
00:04:44.560 --> 00:04:45.560
A sting trooper did it.

107
00:04:45.560 --> 00:04:47.560
Why didn't they pin it on us?

108
00:04:47.560 --> 00:04:48.560
Translation, yeba.

109
00:04:48.560 --> 00:04:49.560
Always botching.

110
00:04:49.560 --> 00:04:50.560
It's been that again.

111
00:04:50.560 --> 00:04:51.560
Nepo baby.

112
00:04:51.560 --> 00:04:52.560
Excuse me?

113
00:04:52.560 --> 00:04:53.560
Dad, stop helping.

114
00:04:53.560 --> 00:04:55.560
This is the opposite of a Nepo baby.

115
00:04:55.560 --> 00:04:59.560
This is a human with half my DNA that despises me for the same reasons

116
00:04:59.560 --> 00:05:00.560
you bailed on her.

117
00:05:00.560 --> 00:05:03.560
This organization resents and discourages talent.

118
00:05:03.560 --> 00:05:06.560
It's why working here was always beneath me, and it's why none of you

119
00:05:06.560 --> 00:05:07.560
are worth eating her shit.

120
00:05:07.560 --> 00:05:12.560
And if you don't start appreciating her, I guarantee you she'll be next out the door.

121
00:05:12.560 --> 00:05:18.560
It was a good rescue, though.

122
00:05:18.560 --> 00:05:19.560
You got me fired!

123
00:05:19.560 --> 00:05:22.560
Only because you blew your chance to quit.

124
00:05:22.560 --> 00:05:23.560
Oh my god.

125
00:05:23.560 --> 00:05:24.560
Oh my god.

126
00:05:24.560 --> 00:05:27.560
I really hope I am the clone, because I never asked to be born.

127
00:05:27.560 --> 00:05:30.560
I can't handle watching you host those parasites.

128
00:05:30.560 --> 00:05:33.560
Clone or not, that's still my blood in your veins.

129
00:05:33.560 --> 00:05:34.560
Yeah, I know.

130
00:05:34.560 --> 00:05:36.560
I'm trying to overcome that.

131
00:05:36.560 --> 00:05:37.560
Ouch.

132
00:05:37.560 --> 00:05:38.560
Oh, boohoo.

133
00:05:38.560 --> 00:05:39.560
Whatever.

134
00:05:39.560 --> 00:05:40.560
Drop me off in space.

135
00:05:40.560 --> 00:05:42.560
What are you going to do?

136
00:05:42.560 --> 00:05:45.560
I'm going to get to the bottom of this inside hit on the queen.

137
00:05:45.560 --> 00:05:48.560
I know a guy that knows a guy that knows some bugs.

138
00:05:48.560 --> 00:05:50.560
Look, I gotta drop you off somewhere.

139
00:05:50.560 --> 00:05:55.560
It might as well be the filth-encrusted apartment of an insect supremacist arms dealer.

140
00:05:55.560 --> 00:05:57.560
Fine.

141
00:05:57.560 --> 00:06:06.560
I thought you were dropping me off.

142
00:06:06.560 --> 00:06:08.560
I gotta make sure it's the right supremacist.

143
00:06:08.560 --> 00:06:10.560
They all look alike.

144
00:06:10.560 --> 00:06:12.560
Hey, no mammals allowed.

145
00:06:12.560 --> 00:06:13.560
That's our guy.

146
00:06:13.560 --> 00:06:14.560
Oh, shit.

147
00:06:14.560 --> 00:06:15.560
Oh, hey.

148
00:06:15.560 --> 00:06:17.560
I didn't mean that about mammals.

149
00:06:17.560 --> 00:06:19.560
You're clearly a good one.

150
00:06:19.560 --> 00:06:20.560
She is.

151
00:06:20.560 --> 00:06:22.560
She's very interested in insect politics.

152
00:06:22.560 --> 00:06:26.560
Um, actually, there's no such thing because insects are genetically inclined for organization.

153
00:06:26.560 --> 00:06:27.560
Whoa!

154
00:06:27.560 --> 00:06:30.560
So tell us which insect organized a hit on the queen.

155
00:06:30.560 --> 00:06:31.560
I don't know.

156
00:06:31.560 --> 00:06:33.560
You guys can't approve you're not going to let me fall.

157
00:06:33.560 --> 00:06:34.560
Oh god.

158
00:06:34.560 --> 00:06:35.560
Oh, jeez.

159
00:06:35.560 --> 00:06:36.560
Oh, jeez.

160
00:06:36.560 --> 00:06:37.560
You're just going to...

161
00:06:37.560 --> 00:06:39.560
I'm ready to write shit.

162
00:06:39.560 --> 00:06:41.560
It was fantabulous.

163
00:06:41.560 --> 00:06:43.560
The formal royal doctor.

164
00:06:43.560 --> 00:06:45.560
Wait, the medical officer?

165
00:06:45.560 --> 00:06:46.560
That's all I know.

166
00:06:46.560 --> 00:06:47.560
I swear.

167
00:06:47.560 --> 00:06:48.560
Is it, though?

168
00:06:48.560 --> 00:06:49.560
Look at that.

169
00:06:49.560 --> 00:06:50.560
Dad.

170
00:06:50.560 --> 00:06:51.560
He said that's all he knew.

171
00:06:51.560 --> 00:06:52.560
I'm a mammal.

172
00:06:52.560 --> 00:06:53.560
I'm disorganized.

173
00:06:53.560 --> 00:06:55.560
I've heard of that doctor, though.

174
00:06:55.560 --> 00:06:57.560
Classic disgraced eugenicist trope.

175
00:06:57.560 --> 00:07:00.560
You can get disgraced for eugenics.

176
00:07:00.560 --> 00:07:01.560
By insects?

177
00:07:01.560 --> 00:07:02.560
I suppose he had a gift.

178
00:07:02.560 --> 00:07:03.560
Did he have an address?

179
00:07:10.560 --> 00:07:11.560
Hi.

180
00:07:11.560 --> 00:07:13.560
Don't be afraid to surrender.

181
00:07:13.560 --> 00:07:14.560
Yeah.

182
00:07:14.560 --> 00:07:16.560
You can even join us as an unlikely ally.

183
00:07:16.560 --> 00:07:17.560
I don't know what that is.

184
00:07:17.560 --> 00:07:18.560
I can explain.

185
00:07:18.560 --> 00:07:19.560
Does your bug culture have ghosts?

186
00:07:19.560 --> 00:07:20.560
Yes.

187
00:07:20.560 --> 00:07:24.560
Has it had any hit movies about busting ghosts successful enough to generate sequels and cartoons?

188
00:07:24.560 --> 00:07:25.560
I don't know.

189
00:07:25.560 --> 00:07:26.560
I don't know.

190
00:07:26.560 --> 00:07:27.560
I don't know.

191
00:07:27.560 --> 00:07:28.560
I don't know.

192
00:07:28.560 --> 00:07:32.560
Has it had any hit movies about busting ghosts successful enough to generate sequels and cartoons?

193
00:07:32.560 --> 00:07:33.560
Of course.

194
00:07:33.560 --> 00:07:37.560
Well, an unlikely ally would be like a ghost that hangs out with the ghostbusters.

195
00:07:37.560 --> 00:07:40.560
That is the most offensive job offer I've ever received.

196
00:07:40.560 --> 00:07:41.560
More offensive than death?

197
00:07:41.560 --> 00:07:42.560
Good luck with that.

198
00:07:42.560 --> 00:07:46.560
Wait, so he's too cool to be a slimer, but he's asthmatic.

199
00:07:55.560 --> 00:07:57.560
That's new.

200
00:07:57.560 --> 00:07:59.560
Creatively trailblazing.

201
00:08:08.560 --> 00:08:10.560
Jesus Christ!

202
00:08:11.560 --> 00:08:14.560
I hope killing these things is leveling us up.

203
00:08:16.560 --> 00:08:18.560
It's some kind of souped up fungus.

204
00:08:18.560 --> 00:08:19.560
What?

205
00:08:19.560 --> 00:08:20.560
Should we be wearing masks?

206
00:08:20.560 --> 00:08:21.560
Nah, we're fine.

207
00:08:21.560 --> 00:08:22.560
It's a bug problem.

208
00:08:22.560 --> 00:08:23.560
These little guys don't affect mammals.

209
00:08:23.560 --> 00:08:25.560
Why would they?

210
00:08:25.560 --> 00:08:28.560
It's a highly evolved symbiote.

211
00:08:28.560 --> 00:08:30.560
Its goal is galactic domination.

212
00:08:30.560 --> 00:08:36.560
So why would it want to be hosted by shit-flinging monkeys from a planet named after dirt?

213
00:08:36.560 --> 00:08:38.560
Wow, we're disease-bragging now.

214
00:08:38.560 --> 00:08:40.560
That fungus is no disease.

215
00:08:40.560 --> 00:08:41.560
It's the cure.

216
00:08:41.560 --> 00:08:44.560
My species has been wasting away for generations.

217
00:08:44.560 --> 00:08:45.560
We're being led by a-

218
00:08:45.560 --> 00:08:47.560
Ah, yeah, millennials killed Blockbuster Video.

219
00:08:47.560 --> 00:08:49.560
Just tell my daughter why you whacked your own queen.

220
00:08:49.560 --> 00:08:52.560
Her majesty refused to distribute my medicine.

221
00:08:52.560 --> 00:08:57.560
So I had her killed in secret and replaced with a robot queen who will.

222
00:08:57.560 --> 00:09:02.560
All of Grumflum 1 will gather for her birthday and all will receive a gift.

223
00:09:02.560 --> 00:09:05.560
That's not how birthdays work, dipshit.

224
00:09:05.560 --> 00:09:07.560
How about this for a birthday?

225
00:09:07.560 --> 00:09:09.560
Close airlock 7.

226
00:09:14.560 --> 00:09:16.560
You really don't owe me, do you?

227
00:09:16.560 --> 00:09:17.560
And you don't know me.

228
00:09:17.560 --> 00:09:19.560
Or the various sizes of bugs.

229
00:09:19.560 --> 00:09:21.560
Ultramplomites, attack!

230
00:09:23.560 --> 00:09:26.560
Behold the Grumflumites of the future!

231
00:09:26.560 --> 00:09:28.560
Soon we will reign again!

232
00:09:28.560 --> 00:09:30.560
She's getting away!

233
00:09:30.560 --> 00:09:32.560
And living rent-free in your head!

234
00:09:42.560 --> 00:09:45.560
Ah, so much for my fucking brick.

235
00:09:53.560 --> 00:09:56.560
Toro, Toro!

236
00:09:56.560 --> 00:09:58.560
Monay!

237
00:10:03.560 --> 00:10:05.560
What was that rent-free in your head shift?

238
00:10:05.560 --> 00:10:07.560
It's dumb people saying something meaningless because they've learned a new phrase.

239
00:10:07.560 --> 00:10:09.560
It just means you're thinking about something.

240
00:10:09.560 --> 00:10:11.560
Focus, Dad. The queen is a spore bomb.

241
00:10:11.560 --> 00:10:13.560
Ooh, you better call the defiance.

242
00:10:13.560 --> 00:10:15.560
Why, so they can form a committee?

243
00:10:15.560 --> 00:10:16.560
You don't want your old job back?

244
00:10:16.560 --> 00:10:18.560
No, Dad. The defiance sucks.

245
00:10:18.560 --> 00:10:21.560
But that doctor keeps trying to kill me. He is not getting a W.

246
00:10:21.560 --> 00:10:23.560
Oh, God, I'm turning it to my father.

247
00:10:23.560 --> 00:10:24.560
That's all you had to say, partner.

248
00:10:24.560 --> 00:10:26.560
Alright, should be pretty easy.

249
00:10:26.560 --> 00:10:29.560
We get it undetected, find the spore bomb, and portal it out of there.

250
00:10:29.560 --> 00:10:33.560
Step one, we blend in as bugs working for the Department of Transportation.

251
00:10:33.560 --> 00:10:36.560
My guy, Cisco, will be at the back door at 7 a.m.

252
00:10:36.560 --> 00:10:37.560
Who's Cisco?

253
00:10:37.560 --> 00:10:38.560
My inside man, don't worry.

254
00:10:38.560 --> 00:10:40.560
Okay, but what if he doesn't show up?

255
00:10:40.560 --> 00:10:42.560
What's that supposed to mean? You don't even know Cisco.

256
00:10:42.560 --> 00:10:46.560
Which is very concerning, since this plan seems very dependent on him.

257
00:10:46.560 --> 00:10:47.560
So, let me finish the plan.

258
00:10:47.560 --> 00:10:48.560
Time.

259
00:10:48.560 --> 00:10:50.560
Step two, Cisco provides us with security criteria.

260
00:10:50.560 --> 00:10:53.560
It provides us with security credentials for the maintenance tunnels.

261
00:10:53.560 --> 00:10:55.560
And if he doesn't show, what's our backup plan?

262
00:10:55.560 --> 00:10:58.560
I use Cisco so that I don't need a backup plan.

263
00:10:58.560 --> 00:10:59.560
What's that?

264
00:10:59.560 --> 00:11:01.560
We ordered food, remember?

265
00:11:01.560 --> 00:11:03.560
I've never heard of this Cisco guy in my life,

266
00:11:03.560 --> 00:11:06.560
and all of a sudden he's the most reliable person ever born.

267
00:11:06.560 --> 00:11:09.560
Baby, I work with more reliable people than you.

268
00:11:09.560 --> 00:11:11.560
Make sure my fries are there.

269
00:11:11.560 --> 00:11:13.560
Thank you. Oh, wait, are there fries?

